  "instructions": [
    "heat the olive oil in a large clay or ceramic pot over medium heat.",
    "add the chopped onions-free aromatics (such as chopped celery and carrot) and cook for 5 minutes, or until they begin to soften.",
    "add the rest-meat and cook for an additional 5 minutes, or until browned on all sides.",
    "add the smoked paprika, cumin, coriander, cayenne pepper (if using), salt, and black pepper, and stir to combine.",
    "add the charred red bell peppers, chopped tomatoes, chicken broth, and lemon juice.",
    "stir to combine, then add the lentils and bring the mixture to a boil.",
    "reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes, or until the lentils are tender.",
    "stir in the chopped parsley and serve hot.",
    "Ensure poultry is cooked to an internal temperature of 74°C / 165°F (juices run clear, no pink remaining) before serving."
  ],
